venice.lib.networkRSB

Class RSBNamespaceBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • venice.lib.networkRSB.RSBNamespaceBuilder

  • public class RSBNamespaceBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    Takes care of namespace- and slot-creating for the RSB network.

    RSB-specific terminology:
    In-slot is Listener.
    Out-slot is Informer.
    In this documentation the generic terminology is used, to be symmetric to the other NamespaceBuilders.

    Scope consists of Namespace and Label. Namespace is the part before the last slash of the Scope and Label is the part after the last slash of the Scope.

    For method parameters Scopes are handled without leading and trailing slashes (they will be added automatically when the RSBNamespaceBuilder interacts with the RSB network).

    • Method Detail

      • initializeInSlots

        public static void initializeInSlots(java.util.ArrayList<AbstractSlot> predefinedSlots)
        Creates in-slots and takes care of setting them up. If an array with AbstractSlots is given, only those in-slots are created. If the array is null (or if the overloaded version without parameters is used), a in-slot is created that listens to the top most namespace (so, only prefix).
        To every in-slot a handler will be added, that informs the main application of new data (if the main application has registered a master-lister).
        Parameters:
        predefinedSlots - an ArrayList with predefined in-slots, or null if not needed

      • initializeInSlots

        public static void initializeInSlots()
        Initializes inslots in dynamic mode. See the parameterized version for more information. Essentially this method calls the parameterized version with null for the parameter.

      • initializeOutSlot

        public static void initializeOutSlot(java.util.ArrayList<AbstractSlot> predefinedSlots)
        Creates out-slots (='informer') and takes care of setting them up. If an array with AbstractSlots is given, only those out-slots are created. If the array is null (or if the overloaded version without parameters is used), out-slots are created dynamically on demand.

        If using predefined out-slots, all data that is written to an unknown out-slot will be ignored.

        If class matching pairs are given, out-slots will be created for the matching class (otherwise for the given type of the abstract slot).

        Parameters:
        predefinedSlots - an ArrayList with predefined in-slots, or null if not needed

      • initializeOutSlot

        public static void initializeOutSlot()
        Initializes dynamic out-slot creation. New out-slots will be created on root namespace (plus prefix, if given). It's the same like initializeOutSlots(null). See overloaded methods for more details.

      • write

        public static boolean write(java.lang.String label,
            java.lang.Object data,
            java.lang.String namespace)
        Sends data to the outslot with the given label and namespace. If that outslot doesn't exists, it will be created (dynamic mode) or ignored (predefined mode).

        The concatenation of the Namespace a slash and the Label gives the Scope.

        Example:
        Namespace 'Venice/test' and Label 'slotA' gives the scope 'Venice/test/slotA'.

        Parameters:
        label - Label of the outslot (w/o leading or trailing slash)
        data - the data to be send (class should match the datatype of the outslot.
        namespace - Namespace of the outslot (w/o leading or trailing slash)
        Returns:
        true if the data was send without problems, otherwise false

      • write

        public static boolean write(java.lang.String scope,
            java.lang.Object data)
        Sends given data to given outslot (='informer'). If that outslot does not exist, it will be created (dynamic mode) or ignored (predefined mode).

        A Scope consists of a Namespace and a Label. The part before the last slash is the Namespace and the part after the last slash is the Label.

        Example:
        The scope 'Venice/test/slotA' consists of the Namespace 'Venice/test' and the Label 'slotA'.

        Parameters:
        scope - the scope of the outslot (='informer'), w/o leading or trailing slash
        data - the data to be send (class should match the datatype of the out-slot.
        Returns:
        true if the data was send without problems, otherwise false
